org.zaproxy.zap

Enum ZAP.ProcessType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ZAP.ProcessType>
      • org.zaproxy.zap.ZAP.ProcessType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ZAP.ProcessType>
    Enclosing class:
    ZAP

    public static enum ZAP.ProcessType
extends Enum<ZAP.ProcessType>
    ZAP can be run in 4 different ways: cmdline: an inline process that exits when it completes the tasks specified by the parameters daemon: a single process with no Swing UI, typically run as a background process desktop: a Swing based desktop tool (which is how is originated, as a fork of Paros Proxy) zaas: a highly scalable distributed system with a web based UI, aka 'ZAP as a Service' (this is 'work in progress')
